# Motion and Interaction Rules

- Use subtle, purposeful motion; avoid decorative animation.
- Drive timing/easing from token values when available.
- Apply hover/pressed overlays correctly:
  - neutral surfaces use surface overlay tokens
  - accent elements use accent overlay tokens
- Use elevation changes for interactive cards (for example depth-1 to depth-2 on hover).

## Accessibility

- Always support `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.
- Ensure focus-visible states are clear and keyboard-friendly.

## Don't

- Do not use large parallax or long-duration animations for standard UI actions.
